Most Buddhist literature holds that [[Maya (mother of the Buddha)|Queen Maya]] died seven days after the birth of her son [[:en:Gautama Buddha|the Buddha]], and was then reborn in the Tushita Heaven. Seven years after the Buddha's enlightenment, she came down to visit [[Trāyastriṃśa|Tavatimsa]] Heaven, where the Buddha later preached the [[:en:Abhidharma|Abhidharma]] to her.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.palikanon.com/english/pali_names/maha/mahamaayaa.htm|title=Māyā|website=www.palikanon.com|access-date=2018-04-07}}</ref>
