'''Tuṣita''' ([[Sanskrit]]) or '''Tusita''' ([[Pāli]]) is one of the six [[:en:Deva (Buddhism)|deva]]-worlds of the [[:en:Desire realm|Desire Realm]] (Kāmadhātu), located between the Yāma heaven and the {{IAST|Nirmāṇarati}} heaven. Like the other heavens, {{IAST|Tuṣita}} is said to be reachable through [[:en:Meditation|Meditation]]. It is the heaven where the [[:en:Bodhisattva|Bodhisattva]] Śvetaketu (Pāli: Setaketu, "White Banner") resided before being reborn on Earth as [[:en:Gautama Buddha|Gautama]], the historical Buddha; it is, likewise, the heaven where the Bodhisattva Nātha ("Protector") currently resides, who will later be born as the next Buddha, [[Maitreya]].
Most Buddhist literature holds that [[:en:Maya (mother of the Buddha)|Queen Maya]] died seven days after the birth of her son [[:en:Gautama Buddha|the Buddha]], and was then reborn in the Tushita Heaven. Seven years after the Buddha's enlightenment, she came down to visit [[Trāyastriṃśa|Tavatimsa]] Heaven, where the Buddha later preached the [[:en:Abhidharma|Abhidharma]] to her.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.palikanon.com/english/pali_names/maha/mahamaayaa.htm|title=Māyā|website=www.palikanon.com|access-date=2018-04-07}}</ref>
