'''Tuṣita''' ([[Sanskrit]]) or '''Tusita''' ([[:en:Pāli|Pāli]]) is one of the six [[:en:Deva (Buddhism)|deva]]-worlds of the [[:en:Desire realm|Desire Realm]] (Kāmadhātu), located between the Yāma heaven and the {{IAST|Nirmāṇarati}} heaven. Like the other heavens, {{IAST|Tuṣita}} is said to be reachable through [[:en:Meditation|Meditation]]. It is the heaven where the [[:en:Bodhisattva|Bodhisattva]] Śvetaketu (Pāli: Setaketu, "White Banner") resided before being reborn on Earth as [[:en:Gautama Buddha|Gautama]], the historical Buddha; it is, likewise, the heaven where the Bodhisattva Nātha ("Protector") currently resides, who will later be born as the next Buddha, [[Maitreya]].
